HEADWORD: Eddy current
<hw>Ed"dy cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>An induced
electric current circulating wholly within a mass of metal; -- called
also <altname>Foucault current</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
